{"word":"μέριμνα","slug":"μέριμνα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μέριμνα</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:derived, derivation'>Deriv.</a> uncertain.\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>care, thought</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> <i>anxious thought, solicitude</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; <el>μ. τινος</el> <i>care for</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>: —<a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>cares, anxieties</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>the thought, mind</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b> <p/></div>"}]}